     <LINES>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>PURPOSE</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>SET LONG TEXT INDICATOR FOR EQUIPMENT</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>After using the LSMW to input long texts for Equipment, the indicator to</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>show that long text exists on the equipment is not displaying.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>Execute this program to update the long text indicator to display.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>Steps:</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>1.  On the selection screen, input the LSMW filename and path.  This</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>program will use the same LSMW file you use to create the equipment long</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>text.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>2.  Click on the execute button.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>It will load the file into a table and use it to run FM:</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>EQKT_SAVE_UPD_TASK to update the long text indicator.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>This is a bare bones program, there is no error reporting if an</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>indicator did not get updated or if it can&apos;t find the equipment number.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>*</TDFORMAT>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
      </TLINE>
